e's a feature request for Claude Code (separate from Cursor) that proposes `SessionStart` and `SessionEnd` hooks. SessionStart could receive initial session info like session_id and cwd, while SessionEnd could receive the final transcript_path and session cost data. However, these appear to be requested features rather than currently implemented hooks.\\n\\nFor the complete official documentation, I'd recommend checking the official Cursor documentation at cursor.com/docs/agent/hooks, as the search results reference it but don't provide the full specification.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"bafe8b56-19f0-4593-9ad0-c59199907e0d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T13:40:56.674Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"query\":\"Cursor editor hooks documentation session-start session-end stop hook payload fields\",\"results\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"srvtoolu_016MWkRN7PDvmqegUs5ewTsm\",\"content\":[{\"title\":\"How to Use Cursor 1.7 Hooks to Customize Your AI Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://skywork.ai/blog/how-to-cursor-1-7-hooks-guide/\"},{\"title\":\"Deep Dive into the new Cursor Hooks | Butler's Log\",\"url\":\"https://blog.gitbutler.com/cursor-hooks-deep-dive\"},{\"title\":\"Cursor Hooks: Supercharge Your AI Dev Workflow in Minutes\",\"url\":\"https://www.theaistack.dev/p/cursor-introduces-hooks\"},{\"title\":\"Cursor 1.7 Adds Hooks for Agent Lifecycle Control - InfoQ\",\"url\":\"https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/cursor-hooks/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - endorlabs/cursor-hook-examples: A repo using cursor hooks with Endor Labs\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/endorlabs/cursor-hook-examples\"},{\"title\":\"Hooks in Cursor and Claude Code: A Step-by-Step Guide\",\"url\":\"https://mlearning.substack.com/p/hooks-in-cursor-and-claude-code-a-step-by-step-guide\"},{\"title\":\"Feature Request: Introduce `SessionStart` and `SessionEnd` Lifecycle Hooks · Issue #4318 · anthropics/claude-code\",\"url\":\"https://git