bin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"42df5647-ab1d-4bfb-aa2e-2ae6298e227f\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"rwr/cursor-token-count\",\"slug\":\"staged-dreaming-token\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Task\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01UtheahCQ4CHNuGiHKDCCRX\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01UtheahCQ4CHNuGiHKDCCRX\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T13:48:23.206Z\",\"uuid\":\"a7d9ff40-e004-4ad8-a247-1247560fb556\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d280be45-239c-4c19-b7b2-d609a5f83963\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"42df5647-ab1d-4bfb-aa2e-2ae6298e227f\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"rwr/cursor-token-count\",\"slug\":\"staged-dreaming-token\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01UtheahCQ4CHNuGiHKDCCRX\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire flow. Let me compile the findings into a clear, thorough report.\\n\\n---\\n\\nHere is a thorough explanation of how state gets passed between hook invocations.\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nEach hook invocation is a completely fresh process. There is no in-memory state between calls. All state is persisted to disk and read back on the next invocation. There are three separate on-disk state stores, each serving a different purpose.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. The Three State Stores\\n\\n### Store 1: Session State Files — `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n\\nThis is the primary, long-lived state store. It persists across the entire lifetime of a session (from first `user-prompt-submit` to after the user commits).\\n\\n**Location:** Determined via `git rev-parse --git-common-dir`, which returns the shared `.git/` directory, even from git worktrees. The directory is `.git/entire-sessions/`. Files are named `<session-id>.json`.\\n\\n**What it tracks** (`session.State` / `strategy.SessionState`):\\n\\n```\\nSessionID               - the agent's session identifier\\nBaseCommit              - current HEAD when session started (updated on pull/rebase/commit)\\nAttributionBaseCommit   - original base for attribution (not migrated)\\nWorktreePath            - absolute path of the worktree\\nWorktreeID              - internal git worktree identifier\\nPhase                   - \\\"idle\\\" | \\\"active\\\" | \\\"ended\\\" (state machine)\\nTurnID                  - random ID generated fresh each turn, shared across all checkpoints in the turn\\nTurnCheckpointIDs       - list of checkpoint IDs created via mid-turn commits (cleared by HandleTurnEnd at stop)\\nLastCheckpointID        - checkpoint ID from the most recent condensation (used for amend restore)\\nStepCount               - number of checkpoints/steps created in this session\\nCheckpointTranscriptStart - transcript line offset where the current checkpoint cycle began\\nFilesTouched            - files modified/created/deleted during this session (accumulated)\\nAgentType               - \\\"Claude Code\\\" etc.\\nTranscriptPath          - path to the live transcript file\\nFirstPrompt             - truncated first user prompt\\nLastInteractionTime     - updated on every hook invocation\\nStartedAt / EndedAt     - lifecycle timestamps\\nUntrackedFilesAtStart   - for rewind protection\\nPromptAttributions      - per-prompt line attribution records\\nPendingPromptAttribution - attribution calculated at prompt start (moved to array at SaveStep)\\nTokenUsage              - accumulated token counts\\n```\\n\\n**Write locations:** `strategy.SaveSessionState()` → `session.StateStore.Save()` → atomic write (`.tmp` rename) to `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Store 2: Pre-Prompt State Files — `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`\\n\\nShort-lived, created at `user-prompt-submit`, consumed and deleted at `stop`.\\n\\n**What it tracks** (`PrePromptState`):\\n\\n```\\nSessionID               - session identifier\\nTimestamp               - when captured\\nUntrackedFiles          - list of untracked files at prompt submission time\\nTranscriptOffset        - transcript line count at prompt submission time\\nLastTranscriptIdentifier - UUID/message ID of the last transcript entry\\n```\\n\\n**Purpose:** On `stop` (TurnEnd), the handler reads this to know \\\"where was the transcript before this turn\\\" so it can extract only the prompts/files from the current turn (not re-process earlier turns). It also provides the pre-existing untracked files list so that new files created during the turn can be detected.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Store 3: Pre-Task State Files — `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`\\n\\nShort-lived, created at `pre-task`, consumed and deleted at `post-task`.\\n\\n**What it tracks** (`PreTaskState`):\\n\\n```\\nToolUseID       - the Claude tool_use_id for the Task invocation\\nTimestamp       - when captured\\nUntrackedFiles  - list of untracked files at task start\\n```\\n\\n**Purpose:** Same pattern as pre-prompt state but scoped to a subagent invocation. Used during `post-task` to detect what files the subagent created/modified.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Hook-by-Hook Flow\\n\\n### `session-start` → `handleLifecycleSessionStart`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id` and `transcript_path`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. Loads session state from `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (may not exist yet on first start).\\n2. Fires `EventSessionStart` through the state machine. The transitions are:\\n   - `IDLE + SessionStart → IDLE` (no-op)\\n   - `ACTIVE + SessionStart → ACTIVE` + `ActionWarnStaleSession` (warns about stale session)\\n   - `ENDED + SessionStart → IDLE` + `ActionClearEndedAt` (session re-entering)\\n3. Saves updated state back to disk.\\n4. Outputs a `systemMessage` response (the \\\"Powered by Entire\\\" banner) back to Claude via stdout JSON.\\n\\n**Files written:** `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (if state existed).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `user-prompt-submit` → `handleLifecycleTurnStart`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `prompt`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. **`CapturePrePromptState`** — reads current untracked files from git, gets current transcript line count via `analyzer.GetTranscriptPosition(transcriptPath)`, writes `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`.\\n2. Calls `strat.EnsureSetup()` to install git hooks if not already installed.\\n3. Calls `initializer.InitializeSession(sessionID, agentType, transcriptPath, prompt)`:\\n   - For a new session: Creates `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` with `BaseCommit` = current HEAD, `WorktreePath`, `WorktreeID`, `AgentType`, `TranscriptPath`, `FirstPrompt`.\\n   - For an existing session: Fires `EventTurnStart` state machine transition (`IDLE → ACTIVE`, `ENDED → ACTIVE`, `ACTIVE → ACTIVE`), generates a new `TurnID`, clears `LastCheckpointID` and `TurnCheckpointIDs`, calls `migrateShadowBranchIfNeeded` (if HEAD changed due to pull/rebase, renames shadow branch).\\n   - Calculates `PendingPromptAttribution` (captures user edits before agent starts).\\n   - Saves state.\\n\\n**Files written:**\\n- `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json` (new)\\n- `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (created or updated)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `stop` (TurnEnd) → `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id` and `transcript_path`.\\n\\n**State operations — this is the most complex hook:**\\n\\n1. Creates `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/` directory.\\n2. Calls `preparer.PrepareTranscript(transcriptPath)` — polls the transcript for the sentinel `\\\"hooks claude-code stop\\\"` entry (up to 3 seconds) to wait for Claude's async flush.\\n3. Reads the full transcript from Claude's transcript file, writes it to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/full.jsonl`.\\n4. Optionally copies `<transcript>.export.json` to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/export.json` (for OpenCode).\\n5. **Loads `pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`** to get `TranscriptOffset` and `UntrackedFiles`.\\n6. Calls `resolveTranscriptOffset()` — uses offset from pre-prompt state; falls back to `session.CheckpointTranscriptStart`.\\n7. Calls `analyzer.ExtractPrompts(transcriptRef, offset)` to extract only prompts from the current turn.\\n8. Calls `analyzer.ExtractSummary(transcriptRef)`.\\n9. Calls `subagentExtractor.ExtractAllModifiedFiles(transcriptRef, offset, subagentsDir)` — parses main transcript + all subagent transcripts.\\n10. Writes `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt` and `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/summary.txt`.\\n11. Calls `DetectFileChanges(preUntrackedFiles)` — runs `git status`, compares against pre-prompt state untracked files to find new/modified/deleted files.\\n12. Calls `filterToUncommittedFiles()` — removes files already committed to HEAD (by mid-turn commits already condensed via PostCommit).\\n13. Writes `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/context.md`.\\n14. Calls `strat.SaveStep(ctx)` — this is the strategy's core checkpoint-saving logic. For manual-commit, it calls `checkpoint.WriteTemporary()` which creates a shadow branch commit containing all the metadata files and current working tree snapshot.\\n15. For auto-commit: calls `updateAutoCommitTranscriptPosition()` to update `CheckpointTranscriptStart` in session state.\\n16. Calls `transitionSessionTurnEnd(sessionID)`:\\n    - Loads session state.\\n    - Fires `EventTurnEnd` (`ACTIVE → IDLE`).\\n    - Calls `strat.HandleTurnEnd(state)` — for manual-commit, calls `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints()` which reads `TurnCheckpointIDs` and updates each checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1` with the full transcript (since mid-turn PostCommit only had a partial transcript).\\n    - Saves updated state.\\n17. Calls `CleanupPrePromptState()` — deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`.\\n\\n**Files written:**\\n- `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/full.jsonl`\\n- `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt`\\n- `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/summary.txt`\\n- `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/context.md`\\n- Shadow branch commit on `entire/<commit-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` (via `WriteTemporary`)\\n- `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (phase: `active → idle`, TurnCheckpointIDs cleared)\\n- Deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `session-end` → `handleLifecycleSessionEnd`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id` and `transcript_path`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. Calls `markSessionEnded(sessionID)`:\\n   - Loads `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`.\\n   - Fires `EventSessionStop` (`IDLE → ENDED`, `ACTIVE → ENDED`).\\n   - Sets `EndedAt` timestamp.\\n   - Saves updated state.\\n\\n**Files written:** `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (phase: `ended`).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `pre-task` (PreToolUse[Task]) → `handleLifecycleSubagentStart`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id`, `transcript_path`, `tool_use_id`, `tool_input`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. Calls `CapturePreTaskState(toolUseID)` — reads current untracked files, writes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n\\n**Files written:** `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `post-task` (PostToolUse[Task]) → `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id`, `transcript_path`, `tool_use_id`, `tool_input`, `tool_response.agentId`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. Determines subagent transcript path from `tool_response.agentId` and the transcript directory structure (`<transcriptDir>/<agentId>.jsonl`).\\n2. Extracts modified files from the subagent transcript using `analyzer.ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`.\\n3. **Loads `pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`** to get pre-existing untracked files.\\n4. Calls `DetectFileChanges(preUntrackedFiles)`.\\n5. Parses the main transcript for a checkpoint UUID (`FindCheckpointUUID`).\\n6. Calls `strat.SaveTaskStep(ctx)` — saves a task checkpoint on the shadow branch at `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/tasks/<tool-use-id>/`.\\n7. Calls `CleanupPreTaskState(toolUseID)` — deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n\\n**Files written:**\\n- Shadow branch task checkpoint files\\n- Deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Git hooks: `prepare-commit-msg`, `commit-msg`, `post-commit`\\n\\nThese are not Claude hooks but are invoked by git when the user (or agent) commits.\\n\\n**`prepare-commit-msg`:** Reads all `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` files for the current worktree, checks for active sessions with content. If found, appends `Entire-Checkpoint: <checkpoint-id>` trailer to the commit message. For agent commits (no TTY + ACTIVE session), bypasses content detection and adds the trailer unconditionally.\\n\\n**`post-commit`:** The condensation hook. Reads `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer from HEAD commit, finds matching sessions, fires `EventGitCommit` through the state machine:\\n- `ACTIVE + GitCommit → ACTIVE` + `ActionCondense`: calls `CondenseSession()` → `WriteCommitted()` which copies shadow branch data to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. Updates `TurnCheckpointIDs` with the new checkpoint ID (to be finalized later at `stop`).\\n- `IDLE + GitCommit → IDLE` + `ActionCondense`: same condensation.\\n- `ENDED + GitCommit → ENDED` + `ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched` or `ActionDiscardIfNoFiles`.\\n\\nAfter condensation, resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart` to the current transcript length, clears `FilesTouched`, saves `LastCheckpointID`. If there are remaining uncommitted files, creates a carry-forward shadow branch and resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart` to 0.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Key Design Point: No Memory, Only Files\\n\\nEvery hook call is a fresh `os.Exec` subprocess. The lifecycle dispatcher (`DispatchLifecycleEvent`) never has state in memory between calls. The state machine in `session/phase.go` is a pure function (`Transition(currentPhase, event, ctx) → result`) — it reads phase from the JSON file and writes the new phase back.\\n\\nThe transcript position (`TranscriptOffset` / `CheckpointTranscriptStart`) is the critical coordination point: `user-prompt-submit` snapshots \\\"current line count\\\" into `pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`, and `stop` reads that to know where the current turn began so it can extract only the incremental prompts/files.\\n\\nThe `TurnCheckpointIDs` field in session state is a small but important bridge: when the user commits mid-turn (via `post-commit`), the checkpoint ID is appended to this list. Then when `stop` fires `HandleTurnEnd`, it replaces the provisional transcript data in those checkpoints with the now-complete transcript — because `post-commit` happened before Claude finished its turn, so the provisional data was incomplete.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. File Layout Summary\\n\\n```\\n.git/\\n  entire-sessions/\\n    <session-id>.json          # Long-lived session state (phase, base commit, files, transcript offset)\\n\\n.entire/\\n  tmp/\\n    pre-prompt-<session-id>.json   # Short-lived: created user-prompt-submit, deleted at stop\\n    pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json    # Short-lived: created pre-task, deleted at post-task\\n  metadata/\\n    <session-id>/\\n      full.jsonl               # Copied transcript (written at stop)\\n      prompt.txt               # Extracted user prompts (written at stop)\\n      summary.txt              # Last assistant message (written at stop)\\n      context.md               # Generated context (written at stop)\\n      tasks/\\n        <tool-use-id>/         # Task checkpoint data (written at post-task)\\n          checkpoint.json\\n          agent-<id>.jsonl\\n\\n.claude/\\n  settings.json                # Hook registrations (SessionStart, UserPromptSubmit, Stop, SessionEnd, PreToolUse[Task], PostToolUse[Task,TodoWrite])\\n\\n.git/refs/heads/\\n  entire/<commit-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>   # Shadow branch (created at stop via WriteTemporary)\\n  entire/checkpoints/v1                           # Permanent metadata branch (written at post-commit via WriteCommitted)\\n```\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a669149 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 137400\\ntool_uses: 29\\nduration_ms: 121568</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"4699f2cb-91ad-4f1a-906a-267dad3a96df\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T13:48:23.205Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"I need to understand how the Claude Code agent integration stores temporary state between hook invocations. Specifically:\\n\\n1. How does state get passed between different hook calls (e.g., session-start → user-prompt-submit → stop → session-end)?\\n2. Where is temporary state stored on disk between hooks?\\n3. What kind of state is tracked (transcript position, session ID, etc.)?\\n4. How does the strategy layer interact with hook state?\\n\\nLook at:\\n- cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/ - the Claude Code agent implementation\\n- cmd/entire/cli/session/ - session state management\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/ - especially how hooks invoke strategy methods\\n- cmd/entire/cli/commands/ - the hooks command handler\\n\\nFocus on the flow from hook invocation through to state persistence. Be very thorough.\",\"agentId\":\"a669149\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire flow. Let me compile the findings into a clear, thorough report.\\n\\n---\\n\\nHere is a thorough explanation of how state gets passed between hook invocations.\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nEach hook invocation is a completely fresh process. There is no in-memory state between calls. All state is persisted to disk and read back on the next invocation. There are three separate on-disk state stores, each serving a different purpose.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. The Three State Stores\\n\\n### Store 1: Session State Files — `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n\\nThis is the primary, long-lived state store. It persists across the entire lifetime of a session (from first `user-prompt-submit` to after the user commits).\\n\\n**Location:** Determined via `git rev-parse --git-common-dir`, which returns the shared `.git/` directory, even from git worktrees. The directory is `.git/entire-sessions/`. Files are named `<session-id>.json`.\\n\\n**What it tracks** (`session.State` / `strategy.SessionState`):\\n\\n```\\nSessionID               - the agent's session identifier\\nBaseCommit              - current HEAD when session started (updated on pull/rebase/commit)\\nAttributionBaseCommit   - original base for attribution (not migrated)\\nWorktreePath            - absolute path of the worktree\\nWorktreeID              - internal git worktree identifier\\nPhase                   - \\\"idle\\\" | \\\"active\\\" | \\\"ended\\\" (state machine)\\nTurnID                  - random ID generated fresh each turn, shared across all checkpoints in the turn\\nTurnCheckpointIDs       - list of checkpoint IDs created via mid-turn commits (cleared by HandleTurnEnd at stop)\\nLastCheckpointID        - checkpoint ID from the most recent condensation (used for amend restore)\\nStepCount               - number of checkpoints/steps created in this session\\nCheckpointTranscriptStart - transcript line offset where the current checkpoint cycle began\\nFilesTouched            - files modified/created/deleted during this session (accumulated)\\nAgentType               - \\\"Claude Code\\\" etc.\\nTranscriptPath          - path to the live transcript file\\nFirstPrompt             - truncated first user prompt\\nLastInteractionTime     - updated on every hook invocation\\nStartedAt / EndedAt     - lifecycle timestamps\\nUntrackedFilesAtStart   - for rewind protection\\nPromptAttributions      - per-prompt line attribution records\\nPendingPromptAttribution - attribution calculated at prompt start (moved to array at SaveStep)\\nTokenUsage              - accumulated token counts\\n```\\n\\n**Write locations:** `strategy.SaveSessionState()` → `session.StateStore.Save()` → atomic write (`.tmp` rename) to `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Store 2: Pre-Prompt State Files — `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`\\n\\nShort-lived, created at `user-prompt-submit`, consumed and deleted at `stop`.\\n\\n**What it tracks** (`PrePromptState`):\\n\\n```\\nSessionID               - session identifier\\nTimestamp               - when captured\\nUntrackedFiles          - list of untracked files at prompt submission time\\nTranscriptOffset        - transcript line count at prompt submission time\\nLastTranscriptIdentifier - UUID/message ID of the last transcript entry\\n```\\n\\n**Purpose:** On `stop` (TurnEnd), the handler reads this to know \\\"where was the transcript before this turn\\\" so it can extract only the prompts/files from the current turn (not re-process earlier turns). It also provides the pre-existing untracked files list so that new files created during the turn can be detected.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Store 3: Pre-Task State Files — `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`\\n\\nShort-lived, created at `pre-task`, consumed and deleted at `post-task`.\\n\\n**What it tracks** (`PreTaskState`):\\n\\n```\\nToolUseID       - the Claude tool_use_id for the Task invocation\\nTimestamp       - when captured\\nUntrackedFiles  - list of untracked files at task start\\n```\\n\\n**Purpose:** Same pattern as pre-prompt state but scoped to a subagent invocation. Used during `post-task` to detect what files the subagent created/modified.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Hook-by-Hook Flow\\n\\n### `session-start` → `handleLifecycleSessionStart`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id` and `transcript_path`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. Loads session state from `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (may not exist yet on first start).\\n2. Fires `EventSessionStart` through the state machine. The transitions are:\\n   - `IDLE + SessionStart → IDLE` (no-op)\\n   - `ACTIVE + SessionStart → ACTIVE` + `ActionWarnStaleSession` (warns about stale session)\\n   - `ENDED + SessionStart → IDLE` + `ActionClearEndedAt` (session re-entering)\\n3. Saves updated state back to disk.\\n4. Outputs a `systemMessage` response (the \\\"Powered by Entire\\\" banner) back to Claude via stdout JSON.\\n\\n**Files written:** `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (if state existed).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `user-prompt-submit` → `handleLifecycleTurnStart`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `prompt`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. **`CapturePrePromptState`** — reads current untracked files from git, gets current transcript line count via `analyzer.GetTranscriptPosition(transcriptPath)`, writes `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`.\\n2. Calls `strat.EnsureSetup()` to install git hooks if not already installed.\\n3. Calls `initializer.InitializeSession(sessionID, agentType, transcriptPath, prompt)`:\\n   - For a new session: Creates `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` with `BaseCommit` = current HEAD, `WorktreePath`, `WorktreeID`, `AgentType`, `TranscriptPath`, `FirstPrompt`.\\n   - For an existing session: Fires `EventTurnStart` state machine transition (`IDLE → ACTIVE`, `ENDED → ACTIVE`, `ACTIVE → ACTIVE`), generates a new `TurnID`, clears `LastCheckpointID` and `TurnCheckpointIDs`, calls `migrateShadowBranchIfNeeded` (if HEAD changed due to pull/rebase, renames shadow branch).\\n   - Calculates `PendingPromptAttribution` (captures user edits before agent starts).\\n   - Saves state.\\n\\n**Files written:**\\n- `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json` (new)\\n- `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (created or updated)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `stop` (TurnEnd) → `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id` and `transcript_path`.\\n\\n**State operations — this is the most complex hook:**\\n\\n1. Creates `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/` directory.\\n2. Calls `preparer.PrepareTranscript(transcriptPath)` — polls the transcript for the sentinel `\\\"hooks claude-code stop\\\"` entry (up to 3 seconds) to wait for Claude's async flush.\\n3. Reads the full transcript from Claude's transcript file, writes it to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/full.jsonl`.\\n4. Optionally copies `<transcript>.export.json` to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/export.json` (for OpenCode).\\n5. **Loads `pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`** to get `TranscriptOffset` and `UntrackedFiles`.\\n6. Calls `resolveTranscriptOffset()` — uses offset from pre-prompt state; falls back to `session.CheckpointTranscriptStart`.\\n7. Calls `analyzer.ExtractPrompts(transcriptRef, offset)` to extract only prompts from the current turn.\\n8. Calls `analyzer.ExtractSummary(transcriptRef)`.\\n9. Calls `subagentExtractor.ExtractAllModifiedFiles(transcriptRef, offset, subagentsDir)` — parses main transcript + all subagent transcripts.\\n10. Writes `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt` and `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/summary.txt`.\\n11. Calls `DetectFileChanges(preUntrackedFiles)` — runs `git status`, compares against pre-prompt state untracked files to find new/modified/deleted files.\\n12. Calls `filterToUncommittedFiles()` — removes files already committed to HEAD (by mid-turn commits already condensed via PostCommit).\\n13. Writes `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/context.md`.\\n14. Calls `strat.SaveStep(ctx)` — this is the strategy's core checkpoint-saving logic. For manual-commit, it calls `checkpoint.WriteTemporary()` which creates a shadow branch commit containing all the metadata files and current working tree snapshot.\\n15. For auto-commit: calls `updateAutoCommitTranscriptPosition()` to update `CheckpointTranscriptStart` in session state.\\n16. Calls `transitionSessionTurnEnd(sessionID)`:\\n    - Loads session state.\\n    - Fires `EventTurnEnd` (`ACTIVE → IDLE`).\\n    - Calls `strat.HandleTurnEnd(state)` — for manual-commit, calls `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints()` which reads `TurnCheckpointIDs` and updates each checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1` with the full transcript (since mid-turn PostCommit only had a partial transcript).\\n    - Saves updated state.\\n17. Calls `CleanupPrePromptState()` — deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`.\\n\\n**Files written:**\\n- `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/full.jsonl`\\n- `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt`\\n- `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/summary.txt`\\n- `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/context.md`\\n- Shadow branch commit on `entire/<commit-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` (via `WriteTemporary`)\\n- `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (phase: `active → idle`, TurnCheckpointIDs cleared)\\n- Deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `session-end` → `handleLifecycleSessionEnd`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id` and `transcript_path`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. Calls `markSessionEnded(sessionID)`:\\n   - Loads `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`.\\n   - Fires `EventSessionStop` (`IDLE → ENDED`, `ACTIVE → ENDED`).\\n   - Sets `EndedAt` timestamp.\\n   - Saves updated state.\\n\\n**Files written:** `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (phase: `ended`).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `pre-task` (PreToolUse[Task]) → `handleLifecycleSubagentStart`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id`, `transcript_path`, `tool_use_id`, `tool_input`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. Calls `CapturePreTaskState(toolUseID)` — reads current untracked files, writes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n\\n**Files written:** `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `post-task` (PostToolUse[Task]) → `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd`\\n\\n**Input from Claude:** JSON on stdin with `session_id`, `transcript_path`, `tool_use_id`, `tool_input`, `tool_response.agentId`.\\n\\n**State operations:**\\n1. Determines subagent transcript path from `tool_response.agentId` and the transcript directory structure (`<transcriptDir>/<agentId>.jsonl`).\\n2. Extracts modified files from the subagent transcript using `analyzer.ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`.\\n3. **Loads `pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`** to get pre-existing untracked files.\\n4. Calls `DetectFileChanges(preUntrackedFiles)`.\\n5. Parses the main transcript for a checkpoint UUID (`FindCheckpointUUID`).\\n6. Calls `strat.SaveTaskStep(ctx)` — saves a task checkpoint on the shadow branch at `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/tasks/<tool-use-id>/`.\\n7. Calls `CleanupPreTaskState(toolUseID)` — deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n\\n**Files written:**\\n- Shadow branch task checkpoint files\\n- Deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Git hooks: `prepare-commit-msg`, `commit-msg`, `post-commit`\\n\\nThese are not Claude hooks but are invoked by git when the user (or agent) commits.\\n\\n**`prepare-commit-msg`:** Reads all `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` files for the current worktree, checks for active sessions with content. If found, appends `Entire-Checkpoint: <checkpoint-id>` trailer to the commit message. For agent commits (no TTY + ACTIVE session), bypasses content detection and adds the trailer unconditionally.\\n\\n**`post-commit`:** The condensation hook. Reads `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer from HEAD commit, finds matching sessions, fires `EventGitCommit` through the state machine:\\n- `ACTIVE + GitCommit → ACTIVE` + `ActionCondense`: calls `CondenseSession()` → `WriteCommitted()` which copies shadow branch data to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. Updates `TurnCheckpointIDs` with the new checkpoint ID (to be finalized later at `stop`).\\n- `IDLE + GitCommit → IDLE` + `ActionCondense`: same condensation.\\n- `ENDED + GitCommit → ENDED` + `ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched` or `ActionDiscardIfNoFiles`.\\n\\nAfter condensation, resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart` to the current transcript length, clears `FilesTouched`, saves `LastCheckpointID`. If there are remaining uncommitted files, creates a carry-forward shadow branch and resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart` to 0.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Key Design Point: No Memory, Only Files\\n\\nEvery hook call is a fresh `os.Exec` subprocess. The lifecycle dispatcher (`DispatchLifecycleEvent`) never has state in memory between calls. The state machine in `session/phase.go` is a pure function (`Transition(currentPhase, event, ctx) → result`) — it reads phase from the JSON file and writes the new phase back.\\n\\nThe transcript position (`TranscriptOffset` / `CheckpointTranscriptStart`) is the critical coordination point: `user-prompt-submit` snapshots \\\"current line count\\\" into `pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`, and `stop` reads that to know where the current turn began so it can extract only the incremental prompts/files.\\n\\nThe `TurnCheckpointIDs` field in session state is a small but important bridge: when the user commits mid-turn (via `post-commit`), the checkpoint ID is appended to this list. Then when `stop` fires `HandleTurnEnd`, it replaces the provisional transcript data in those checkpoints with the now-complete transcript — because `post-commit` happened before Claude finished its turn, so the provisional data was incomplete.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. File Layout Summary\\n\\n```\\n.git/\\n  entire-sessions/\\n    <session-id>.json          # Long-lived session state (phase, base commit, files, transcript offset)\\n\\n.entire/\\n  tmp/\\n    pre-prompt-<session-id>.json   # Short-lived: created user-prompt-submit, deleted at stop\\n    pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json    # Short-lived: created pre-task, deleted at post-task\\n  metadata/\\n    <session-id>/\\n      full.jsonl               # Copied transcript (written at stop)\\n      prompt.txt               # Extracted user prompts (written at stop)\\n      summary.txt              # Last assistant message (written at stop)\\n      context.md               # Generated context (written at stop)\\n      tasks/\\n        <tool-use-id>/         # Task checkpoint data (written at post-task)\\n          checkpoint.json\\n          agent-<id>.jsonl\\n\\n.claude/\\n  settings.json                # Hook registrations (SessionStart, UserPromptSubmit, Stop, SessionEnd, PreToolUse[Task], PostToolUse[Task,TodoWrite])\\n\\n.git/refs/heads/\\n  entire/<commit-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>   # Shadow branch (created at stop via WriteTemporary)\\n  entire/checkpoints/v1                           # Permanent metadata branch (written at post-commit via WriteCommitted)\\n```\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":121568,\"totalTokens\":137400,\"totalToolUseCount\":29,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3822,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":129422,\"output_tokens\":4155,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":3822,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"d280be45-239c-4c19-b7b2-d609a5f83963\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4699f2cb-91ad-4f1a-906a-267dad3a96df\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"42df5647-ab1d-4bfb-aa2e-2ae6298e227f\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"rwr/cursor-token-count\",\"slug\":\"staged-dreaming-token\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_019MY98kQeQRdv9sR2JsQzRm\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The state between hook invocations is stored entirely on disk across **three locations**:\\n\\n### 1. Session state — `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\nLong-lived, persists for the session's entire lifetime. Tracks:\\n- `Phase` (idle/active/ended) — the state machine\\n- `BaseCommit`, `WorktreePath`, `WorktreeID`\\n- `CheckpointTranscriptStart` — transcript offset for incremental extraction\\n- `TurnID`, `TurnCheckpointIDs` — for coordinating mid-turn commits with the final stop\\n- `StepCount`, `FilesTouched`, `TokenUsage`, `PromptAttributions`\\n- `TranscriptPath`, `AgentType`, `FirstPrompt`, timestamps\\n\\n### 2. Pre-prompt state — `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`\\nShort-lived. Created at `user-prompt-submit`, deleted at `stop`. Tracks:\\n- `TranscriptOffset` — line count at prompt time (so `stop` knows where the turn started)\\n- `UntrackedFiles` — git untracked files at prompt time (so `stop` can detect new files)\\n- `LastTranscriptIdentifier` — UUID of last transcript entry\\n\\n### 3. Pre-task state — `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`\\nShort-lived. Created at `pre-task`, deleted at `post-task`. Same pattern scoped to a subagent invocation.\\n\\n### The flow\\n\\n```\\nuser-prompt-submit:\\n  1. Snapshot transcript position + untracked files → .entire/tmp/pre-prompt-*.json\\n  2. Load/create session state → .git/entire-sessions/*.json\\n  3. Fire TurnStart (IDLE→ACTIVE), generate TurnID, save\\n\\nstop:\\n  1. Read pre-prompt state to get TranscriptOffset\\n  2. Extract prompts/files from transcript since offset\\n  3. Save checkpoint (shadow branch commit via WriteTemporary)\\n  4. Fire TurnEnd (ACTIVE→IDLE), save session state\\n  5. Delete pre-prompt state\\n\\npost-commit (git hook, not agent hook):\\n  1. Read session state, fire GitCommit event\\n  2. Condense shadow branch → entire/checkpoints/v1\\n  3. Append checkpoint ID to TurnCheckpointIDs\\n  4. Save session state\\n\\nsession-end:\\n  1. Fire SessionStop (→ENDED), save session state\\n```\\n\\nEvery hook is a fresh subprocess — there's no in-memory state. The `TranscriptOffset` in pre-prompt state is the critical coordination point: it lets `stop` extract only the incremental changes since the last prompt.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creatio