ranscript/parse.go` that copies `Role → Type` when `Type` is empty\\n   - Calling it from both `ParseFromBytes` and `ParseFromFileAtLine`\\n   - Adding 4 tests in `parse_test.go` for normalization\\n   - Adding 2 tests in `summarize_test.go` for Cursor JSONL condensation\\n\\n9. **User: \\\"commit and push this\\\"** - Committed as 0070be03. Push initially failed (non-fast-forward), pulled with rebase, then pushed successfully.\\n\\nKey files modified across the conversation:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor_test.go` (created)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle_test.go` (modified - added ReadTranscript tests)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse.go` (modified - normalizeLineType)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse_test.go` (modified - normalization tests)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize_test.go` (modified - Cursor JSONL tests)\\n- PR 392 description updated\\n\\nErrors encountered:\\n1. Two lint errors for unchecked os.ReadFile returns in cursor_test.go round-trip test\\n2. Push rejected (non-fast-forward) - fixed with pull --rebase\\n\\nSummary:\\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\\n   - Improve test coverage for the Cursor agent's checkpoint lifecycle using the `sample.jsonl` reference transcript from a real Cursor session\\n   - Refactor tests so they live in the appropriate test file matching their implementation file (e.g., ReadTranscript tests in lifecycle_test.go)\\n   - Update PR 392's description to reflect all changes made\\n   - Research whether Cursor hooks provide token usage data (for potential TokenCalculator implementation)\\n   - Understand how the Claude Code integration stores temporary state between hook invocations\\n   - Fix a bug where `BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes` produces empty output for Cursor transcripts because it switches on `line.Type` (empty for Cursor) instead of `line.Role`\\n   - Commit and push all changes\\n\\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\\n   - **Cursor transcript format**: Uses `\\\"role\\\"` (not `\\\"type\\\"`) for user/assistant distinction, wraps user text in `<user_query>` tags, has no `tool_use` blocks, no UUID field, no token usage data\\n   - **Claude Code transcript format**: Uses `\\\"type\\\"` for user/assistant, has tool_use blocks, UUIDs, token usage\\n   - **Role→Type normalization**: When `Type` is empty but `Role` is set, copy Role into Type during parsing so all downstream consumers work uniformly\\n   - **Cursor hooks**: 16 agent hooks available (sessionStart, sessionEnd, stop, beforeSubmitPrompt, etc.), all share base fields including `model`, but **no token/cost/usage fields** exist in any hook payload\\n   - **Inter-hook state storage**: Three disk-based stores — `.git/entire-sessions/*.json` (long-lived), `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-*.json` (prompt→stop), `.entire/tmp/pre-task-*.json` (pre-task→post-task)\\n   - **Agent interface pattern**: Agents implement `Agent` interface plus optional interfaces (`HookSupport`, `TranscriptAnalyzer`, `TokenCalculator`)\\n   - **TranscriptAnalyzer**: Cursor cannot implement this because its transcript lacks tool_use blocks; file detection relies on git status\\n\\n3. Files and Code Sections:\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor_test.go`** (created)\\n     - 30 tests covering identity methods, GetSessionID, ResolveSessionFile, GetSessionDir, ReadSession (5 tests including NativeData verification and ModifiedFiles empty check), WriteSession (6 tests including round-trip, nil, wrong agent, empty agent name), ChunkTranscript/ReassembleTranscript (7 tests), DetectPresence, sanitizePathForCursor\\n     - Uses shared test helpers `sampleTranscriptLines()` and `writeSampleTranscript()` that produce real Cursor JSONL format\\n     ```go\\n     func sampleTranscriptLines() []string {\\n         return []string{\\n             `{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"<user_query>\\\\nhello\\\\n</user_query>\\\"}]}}`,\\n             `{\\\"role\\\":\\