ranscriptFromBytes_CursorRoleBasedJSONL` — verifies 4 entries from Cursor JSONL with `<user_query>` tags\\n       - `TestBuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes_CursorNoToolUseBlocks` — verifies no tool entries and non-empty result\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize.go`** (read, not modified)\\n     - `BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes` at line 122 already routes `AgentTypeCursor` to the Claude/JSONL path — the fix was in the parser layer so this didn't need changes\\n     - `BuildCondensedTranscript` at line 229 switches on `line.Type` — this now works for Cursor because Type is normalized from Role during parsing\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/transcript/types.go`** (read, not modified this session)\\n     - `Line` struct has both `Type` and `Role` fields, documented that Claude uses Type, Cursor uses Role\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go`** (read, not modified this session)\\n     - ReadSession, WriteSession, ChunkTranscript, ReassembleTranscript implementations\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle.go`** (read, not modified this session)\\n     - ReadTranscript, ParseHookEvent, and internal parse functions\\n\\n   - **PR 392 description** (updated via `gh pr edit 392`)\\n     - Removed TranscriptAnalyzer mention, added Design decisions section, updated file listings and test counts\\n\\n4. Errors and fixes:\\n   - **Lint errors in cursor_test.go**: Two `errcheck` violations for unchecked `os.ReadFile` returns in `TestWriteSession_RoundTrip`. Fixed by adding proper error handling with `t.Fatalf`.\\n   - **Push rejected (non-fast-forward)**: Remote had new commits when pushing the final fix. Fixed with `git pull --rebase origin robin/cursor-agent` then pushing again.\\n   - **No user correction errors in this session** — the bug about Role→Type normalization was proactively identified by the user before it caused a runtime issue.\\n\\n5. Problem Solving:\\n   - **Cursor transcript format compatibility**: The core problem was that